<rating>5<//rating><Review>I've used Smiles Dental Care for at least 15 years for all my dental needs. Recently, I've moved my mother's dental care to Smiles Dental Care as well. I've always received excellent dental care but it is Smiles Dental Care's excellent service to my mother for her wisdom tooth extraction that drove me to this review.

First off, in this time of COVID, Smiles Dental Care is outstanding in its preparation to protect both its doctors and staff and in turn protect its patient. Air purifiers are running, multiple auto dispense hand sanitizers are available, and all staff are wearing masks and face shields.

Second, the entire facility is clean and not cramped and equipment are modern.

However, their care for my 80 year old mother is what this review is all about. In particular, Dr. Mehran Chitgar was patient with my mother, very respectful of her trepidation, and took the time to make her feel comfortable. She was thorough in evaluating her medical state (fortunately, my mother is in great health using only low dosages of blood pressure and cholesterol mediation) and made sure that my mother was properly anesthetized. My mother felt no pain during the entire process. The dentist and her staff was incredibly skilled and professional and caring. The post-op explanation and followup was also very much appreciated.

And I believe this is just the way they treat all their patients.

I'm going to be using Smiles Dental Care for the foreseeable future and would not hesitant to recommend this office will be recommending them to anyone I know.< /Review><Pics>None</Pics>< resp>

<review>I love a disorganized thrift store (they're always filled with treasures) but be warned - this place requires some effort. Every rail is over-stuffed, clothes are not organized by size, and there are no dressing rooms. I'm also a size 2/4, and a lot of the things I was looking for were hiding in the kids' section. Good stuff, and great daily deals, but don't expect a tailored shopping experience.</review>< Pics>

<Date>1503133827475</Date><Response>None< /Response><user_name>Karina Everly<//user_name><user_id>111171371765882837942<//user_id><GmapID>0x80c2957efba99f99:0xbcf28a4a425f4362< /GmapID>< Pictures>
None<//Pictures>
< text>
This is my favorite thrift shop, I shop there every week. But I have to say, that it's a total bummer that the prices have increased quite a bit. - E.G one item as a perfect example; a regular 'straw sun hat' $17.99!!?! You can get one of those new at 'Forever 21' at the same price or less!! I saw 2 'orange karate belts' this week and they were each $5.00! New they cost $5.00 in a martial arts store!! T-shirts are $5.00 and up, where they shouldn't be more than $2.00 really. The bags/purses cost $10.00 - $20.00 and up!?!?

Another thing; their policy regarding the '50% off stamp' you receive on the back of your receipt when you spend $20.00 or more, - it's now only valid for that following Sunday, where before, you could come and shop any Sunday at your own convenience and still enjoy the 50% off. I wonder why all the changes in this direction, considering it has gotten a lot more business since Magnolia Park has become very popular!!

That all being said, it's still a fun thrift shop and you can get lost in there for hours. - And it's still inexpensive to shop there. But, where before I would grab everything I liked, even an item that I wasn't quite sure about, now it's not worth it as I would be bummed about wasting like $10.00 in the event that the item doesn't work out.

But go and shop and have fun! It's like going on a treasure hunt finding things you didn't know you needed 😜</text>

<date>1621134603156</date>< name>
Just My Opinion< /name>
<Text>If you love rib eye then you have to go here. For a chain restaurant this is the best place for a reliable perfectly cooked rib eye. I'm pretty picky. I like it seasoned with just salt and pepper and medium rare. And I can say i have always had a perfectly cooked steak here. Is it pricey. Yes. Its 31 dollars for a 20 oz bone in rib eye but it is definitely worth it. They will even bring you a second plate if you want to share it. Their baked potatoes, salads are also good. But those are hard to mess up. Their rolls and cinnamon butter are amazing but I have to limit myself on how many I can eat.
If you go on the weekend there will be a wait but in my opinion it is worth it. Just have some patience and be hungry.< /Text><Resp>{'time': 1621296309389, 'text': 'Just, thanks for leaving an awesome review! We hope to see you again soon!'}<//Resp>< pictures>

< review>
I came to the Texas Roadhouse as a suggestion of places to eat from a family member. The customer service I experienced was great, though if you are going to dine in (I did this during Covid-19 times), there is a wait time. And if I remember correctly, up to 6-7 people max per group. The food also takes time to get to your table, though I did have five other people with me so I understand that it takes time to make all of our food and bring them at the same time.
Anyways, I ate one of the combo plates and it was pretty good, though I do not think it is the "BEST" food I ever tasted. The food was definitely filling though so I couldn't finish everything. We took 3 boxes of leftovers to eat later at home.</review>

<Text>I wanted to give this place more stars. I had high hopes, after reading reviews, so did my wife. She's on a healthier eating path than I, she ordered a 8oz steak with grilled chicken, a side of string beans and brown rice. Out of those 4 items she only enjoyed the chicken. She loves steak mind you. Her comments of the rice and string beans being too salty, hurt. No one wants to be let down when having a cheat meal.

My meal was a slab of ribs and some mac and cheese, with fries. A manly mans feast #Murica! I figured, I'd bring the leftovers home, hoping warmed properly I may experience something more delightful. I was wrong. While warming them up the meat smelled funny, they tasted sour. <Rating>1< /Rating><user>106346093578425940744< /user><response>None< /response><name>Dodge This<//name>< text>
Allow me to begin my review by stating that me and my family have frequented and enjoyed this restaurant for many years since they opened, however my recent experience has truly off put me simply by the way they are managing to get people into the door.

Since the start of COVID and the closure of mostly all dine-in seating establishments it was delightful news to hear that T.R. was now open for limited seating.

On 2/26/21 I decided to treat myself to a long overdue steak dinner and checked in at the outside window around 2:30PM. I received the txt confirmation that I was now on the waiting list to be seated and that it would be a 5-15min wait time which I figured was great considering that it was just me. I then decided wait in my car for a follow up txt announcing an availability.

Unfortunately, I ended up waiting for over 30mins with still no txt until I finally decided to return to the door and speak to one of the staff members for an update. After briefly speaking to one of the hostesses around (3:05PM) and informing her of my situation she replied that I wait just a few more minutes for her return so I did.

Another 30mins ended up passing by to the point that I was now the only patron sitting outside on the bench, and in those moments I watched newly arrived visitors check in then be  seated within moments alongside with others now leaving with full stomachs before I finally decided to head home disappointed. At the end of the day an hour of my time was wasted and my only day off work had a disappointing end.</text>

Okay, first the ribeye steak. Best ever.

<Text>NEW POST JULY 6, 2020:
It is challenging for all the restaurants during this COVID Pandemic, TRH is well prepared to provide the best possible quality and tasty food. The Rib Eye Steak was nicely seasoned and cooked perfectly. As well as the Mashed Potatoes and Fresh Veges. I would like to comment on the plastic utensils. I live 25 minutes away and I often eat in my car while the food is freshly cooked, but the plastic knife and fork is not up to the task of cutting steaks, it bends under pressure, the knife didn’t have the deep teeth to cut, and there are groves in the bottom of the box making it more challenging to cut. < Review>
Okay, first the ribeye steak. Best ever.
Great service, granted, I got there just before the crowds. Staff polite and friendly.
Two margaritas for my guests plus comfort food. Relaxed atmosphere, pleasant decor and ambiance. Pricing comparable to Outback, but a much tastier steak. Not a Sizzler or Bonanza all you can eat place, but the serving size won't disappoint you either,  and the house salad is fresh and more than just iceberg lettuce. Only regret is that they have so few locations in the county.<//Review>

<user_id>111826847850924470527<//user_id>< Text>
Decided we wanted to try a low key steakhouse for the wife's birthday and this one popped up with good reviews. Didn't want a big pricey fancy spot just a decent steak with a casual atmosphere. I ended up getting the sirloin and ribs, wife got the fillet. Honestly, my sirloin was 95% as tender as her fillet, just fantastic. Ribs were good but honestly a but too fall off the bone for me. Sides were decent, nothing special, and presentation was pretty weak for a $25 plate if you ask me. Service was great, people were nice and the steaks were fantastic. Definitely would return.</Text>

< Text>
Last night I had a steak dinner at Texas Roadhouse. I had a medium rare, top cut sirloin. It was melt-in-your-mouth delicious. The meat was so moist and flavorful. My compliments to the chef. To accompany the steak I had a loaded baked potato and green beans. The potato was baked to perfection and was served with butter, bacon, sour cream, and cheese. Pretty much the best combination ever. The green beans were not your typical plain and simple green beans. They were served in a soup like sauce with bacon. You can never go wrong with bacon. Overall a tasty and satisfying meal. I will definitely be eating here again sometime soon.</Text>

< Review>
The restaurant was busy on Sunday night as usual. We waited only 10 or 15 min. once our party of 8 had all arrived.

The waiter took the drinks order and returned later to take our dinner order. 2 coffees had been ordered but we still needed cream and it came much later, only after the food had arrived and the waiter was reminded. We also needed horseradish for the prime rib. It also came 1/2 way through the meal. Why doesn't the waiter either ASK when taking the order or automatically just bring any extras that may be required when delivering the order? Instead, seeing the missing items the customer is left sitting there waiting for the needed items while the coffee and food just gets cold.

The food quality has always been consistently flavorful with large portions. We will return but will be SURE to ask for all the "extras" that we need/ expect at the time we order since it is hard to get anyone's attention once they leave your table. It is so noisy and the workers are so focused on their own section no one seems to notice a customer needs additional service.<//Review>

Wife and I were hungry and had no clue what was available near Riverside and a family member recommended this place.  They also recommended that we download the app and make our reservation and boy were they correct.  The place was packed and had we not check in online we would have been waiting an hour+. We had such a good experience that we ordered 2 meals to go to thank her parents for watching the kids and the food came out the same time we finished our meals.  Definitely will come back for date night.</Review>

< name>
Dan The RV Man!</name>
< Time>
1474939637871< /Time>
< Rating>
4<//Rating>
<Review>Great food with a real "Big Texas" feel. As you walk in the front door you are treated to the wonderful sight of an old style meat counter right next to the check in and waiting area. The barrels of peanuts are nice especially during baseball games but is definitely a ploy to get you walking to the bar.

The feel of the whole establishment is one of family dinner until you step out side to the exterior bar. The bar is nice wrap around bar with 2-3 bartenders. The large screen TVs surrounding the bar area all generally have on the major baseball, football, games and races. The only thing lacking is a decent beer menu and whiskey variety.

The food is amazing. The steak is wonderful and each plate is very generously proportioned and the sides are great. The baked potatoes and mashed potatoes (I grew up in an irish family haha) are amazing.

One of my favorite parts of taking my family here is the big events they put on for birthdays. The crew brings out a saddle and let the birthday kid ride then treat them to a nice desert.

Over all its a great family environment wonderful food and a good drinks. I would recommend this place everyday of the week.< /Review><Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None</Resp>< Gmap_id>
0x80dcb7923e213be7:0x48d84cc7d652e501</Gmap_id>

<Text>We had gotten early enough to arrive to Texas Roadhouse despite calling ahead of time, and were told to wait for an available table for six people. So we waited with the electronic pager for about 45 minutes until one of us came back from the restroom and had saw several empty tables in the back of the restaurant that was large enough for 6. We asked a waiter and they had realized they had forgotten about us. THIS IS THE BEGINNING WHERE IT GOT WORSE.

So we went to our table and began our orders and we were having a good time eating the appetizers and then the main course. My sister took a large spoonful of mashed potatoes and ate it, only to immediately spit it out. Apparently the mashed potatoes had a very gritty and sand-like texture to its taste. We wave in a waiter to notify this and they take the small bowl of mashed potato away and that they will notify the manager to come to us. That was an hour and 30 minutes ago.

So our mood was dimmed and we had wanted to leave after dinner so we ordered 3 to-go boxes. When it was delivered, a now different waiter said that he will go and get the bags for the boxes. We waited for 30 minutes only to ask a waiter who was cleaning a table next to us if we could have a bag for our to-go boxes. The waiter then walked to a booth across from us, went underneath and pulled out a bag for our boxes in under 30 seconds. Needless to say, we were in a pretty bad mood after that.

Now I've been to many Texas Roadhouses, particularly the ones in the east coast and Texas, and their service has always been excellent. This is the first time I've eaten in California and this has the worst service. I'm of Asian ethnicity and my family was the only that day, so I'm not sure if this is blatant racism or shear incompetence from the staff. I have always enjoyed eating at Texas Roadhouse, but this particular restaurant in 370 N. McKinley St, Corona, CA has my negative reviews.

You have been warned! So if you choose to eat at this restaurant do so with all your patience and risk.<//Text>< Pictures>
